-### Shared Beads Write Lane
-
-Normal `br create`, `br update`, and `br close` calls are Beads mutations, not
-manual file edits. Do not reserve `.beads/issues.jsonl` or `.beads/beads.db`
-as ordinary edit files around a `br` command. `br` owns the SQLite transaction
-and JSONL export path; Agent Mail reservations only coordinate humans and
-agents around shared files.
-
-When multiple panes need to mutate Beads in the same repo, use one serialized
-Beads write lane:
-
-1. Queue the requested mutation in the bead thread or orchestrator callback.
-2. One writer owner runs exactly one bounded `br` mutation at a time.
-3. Use `br --lock-timeout 10000 ...` for agent automation when the installed
-   `br` supports it.
-4. Release the lane immediately after the mutation and any required
-   `br sync --flush-only`.
-5. If the lane is busy, report `beads_write_lane_queued` instead of holding an
-   exclusive `.beads/` file reservation.
-
-Joshua-lens: lock contention masquerading as the bug of the week is the same
-operator-pain class as a queue depth metric ignored until the storm hits. A
-junior worker should not need a lock-doctorate to close a bead; the operating
-system should expose one write lane and a queue.
