-## Anti-Patterns
+## Troubleshooting
 
-| Anti-Pattern | Fix |
-|-------------|-----|
-| Vague beads without acceptance criteria | Every bead needs testable AC: "run X, expect Y." Can't write AC = not granular enough. |
-| Oversimplifying during polish | If description >500 words or >5 files, split. Complexity exists for reasons. |
-| Creating beads before plan convergence | Converge in markdown first (4-6 rounds). Convert to beads ONCE — beads are the final format. |
-| Circular dependencies | Run `br dep cycles` after every batch. Must return empty. Break the weakest link. |
-| Ignoring PageRank for triage | Use `bvp --robot-next` — it sees dependency cascades you don't. |
-| Multiple agents on overlapping files | Same-file beads MUST have `dependsOn` chains + Agent Mail file reservations. |
-| Skipping test beads | Polish prompt requires tests. If missing after polish, add manually. |
-| Not syncing to git | `br sync --flush-only` + `git add .beads/` + `git commit` after every batch. |
-| 17+ beads per PRD | O(n²) coordination. Cap at 3-5 per wave. Split into sequential waves. |
+### Worktree Error Fix
 
----
+If you get `failed to create worktree: 'main' is already checked out`:
 
-## FOREVER-RULE: br-prefix-mismatch — JSONL Pollution Guard
-
-> **Source:** 3 fuckup-log incidents 2026-05-06 (`br-prefix-mismatch`). Trauma class: cross-repo `br` ops append foreign-prefix rows to `.beads/issues.jsonl`, causing every subsequent `br create` / `br lint` / `br ready` to fail with `CONFIG_ERROR`.
+```bash
+git branch beads-sync main
+git push -u origin beads-sync
+br config set sync-branch beads-sync
+```
 
-**Trigger phrases:** `CONFIG_ERROR` from `br create` | wrong-prefix bead ID returned | `br lint` fails immediately | `br ready` returns nothing when beads exist | `issue_prefix mismatch` in `br doctor`
+Always use a dedicated sync branch that you never check out directly.
 
-**Rule:** Before ANY `br` command in a session, validate prefix purity. If FAIL, run repair before proceeding.
+### Quick Health Check
 
 ```bash
-# 1. Validate (fast, read-only — run before br create/lint/ready)
-scripts/skillos_beads_prefix_guard.py validate .beads/issues.jsonl
-
-# 2. On FAIL — repair (backup auto-created, idempotent)
-scripts/skillos_beads_prefix_guard.py repair .beads/issues.jsonl
-
-# 3. Confirm clean, then proceed
-scripts/skillos_beads_prefix_guard.py doctor --json
+br config list        # All settings
+br dep cycles         # Must be empty
+which br              # Verify br is installed
 ```
 
-**Anti-patterns:**
-- Forcing `br create` after `CONFIG_ERROR` without running repair first — the error will persist
-- Manually editing `.beads/issues.jsonl` to match the prefix — use `repair`, not hand-editing
-- Grepping out foreign rows without backup — `repair` backs up automatically
+See [TROUBLESHOOTING.md](references/TROUBLESHOOTING.md) for full diagnostics.
 
-**Escalate to `beads-br` § DB-Wedge JSONL Fallback** if `br doctor` shows DB corruption alongside prefix mismatch (both trauma classes can co-occur).
+---
 
