-## Advanced Commands by Intent
-
-The `/brenner` exact-prompt workflow above stays canonical for orchestrating sessions. These advanced subcommands surface state and provenance the workflow already produces — use them when you need to record, audit, or cite that state directly. Each row names one canonical example; the upstream `--help` lists every flag.
-
-| Intent | Command family | Canonical example | What it gives you |
-|---|---|---|---|
-| **Run a controlled test** | `experiment` | `brenner experiment run --thread-id <id> --test-id T-001 --out-file out.json -- pytest -k auth` | Captured exit code, stdout, stderr, cwd, replayability flag — feeds back into the artifact |
-| **Encode a result for the artifact** | `experiment encode` | `brenner experiment encode --result-file out.json` | Generates the artifact-shaped record (test_id, expected, actual, verdict) for an EDIT delta |
-| **Stand up an evidence pack** | `evidence init` | `brenner evidence init --thread-id <id>` | Creates the evidence ledger this thread will accumulate |
-| **Log a typed evidence row** | `evidence add` | `brenner evidence add --thread-id <id> --type literature --title "Brenner 1974" --source <doi> --supports H1 --refutes H2` | Stores an EV-NNN row with explicit `supports/refutes/informs` edges to hypotheses |
-| **Anchor a verbatim excerpt** | `evidence add-excerpt` | `brenner evidence add-excerpt --thread-id <id> --evidence-id EV-007 --text "..." --verbatim --location "p.4 ¶2"` | Pins quoted text against EV-NNN so close-gates can verify byte-for-byte fidelity |
-| **Independently verify an EV-NNN** | `evidence verify` | `brenner evidence verify --thread-id <id> --evidence-id EV-007 --notes "reproduced 2026-05-08"` | Records that a second agent re-checked the evidence (anti-rubber-stamp) |
-| **Quarantine an anomaly** | `anomaly create` | `brenner anomaly create --observation "<s>" --conflicts-with H1,H2 --conflict-description "<s>"` | Forces unexpected results into the active register instead of the summary |
-| **Attack a hypothesis or test** | `critique create` | `brenner critique create --target H-002 --attack "<s>" --evidence-to-confirm "<s>" --severity serious` | Treats critiques as first-class objects with disposition (modified/killed/new_test) |
-| **Surface a hidden assumption** | `assumption create` | `brenner assumption create --statement "<s>" --type methodological --load-description "<s>"` | Pre-registers what the plan is assuming so it can be later challenged or falsified |
-| **Render the full evidence ledger** | `evidence render / list` | `brenner evidence list --thread-id <id> --json` | Dumps the relational evidence pack for audits or close-gate consumption |
-
-**When to reach for these.** If the canonical exact-prompt is enough to keep the session moving, prefer it — these subcommands add ceremony. Reach for them when (a) you need to *cite* a result downstream (`experiment encode`), (b) you need the relation graph machine-checkable (`evidence add` with `--supports/--refutes/--informs`), (c) something doesn't fit the leading hypothesis and you need to quarantine it (`anomaly create`), or (d) you want a critique or assumption tracked across rounds rather than buried in prose.
-
-**Doctrine link.** Local flywheel wires consume this surface: `flywheel-d3q0j` (EV anchors in compliance packs), `flywheel-gau3q` (prediction-lock receipts), `flywheel-ykkhv` (hypothesis slate + kill criteria). Those wires assume the brenner side records via `evidence add` / `experiment encode` / `assumption create` rather than prose summaries.
